author: ETA PRIME
description:
he new Beelink SER9 Max is here, and it’s packing a Ryzen 7 255H (Zen 4) with an RDNA 3 iGPU (12 CUs) — plus some seriously rare features for a mini PC like 10GbE, USB4 (40Gbps), DisplayPort 2.1, and HDMI up to 4K 240Hz.
In this review I’ll show the ports, upgrade access (DDR5 + dual M.2 2280), BIOS power modes (Balanced vs Performance / 65W sustained), VRAM allocation, real-world benchmarks, and 1080p gaming performance (Fallout 4, Spider-Man 2, Forza Horizon 5, Street Fighter 6). We’ll also check temps + total wall power so you know what this thing is like day-to-day.
